# GCP VM — Git rules (`wrrapd-server-1`, `/home/phill/wrrapd-GCP`)

## Never `git pull` on the GCP VM

- **Do not run `git pull`** on the production GCP VM. Do not recommend it in runbooks or agent replies for this host.
- Pull can merge `origin` over local working-tree changes, Capacitor/mobile churn, or half-applied deploy state.

## Always `git push` to GitHub **from the GCP VM** when shipping

- After edits on the VM are committed, the agent must treat **`git push` from this VM to `origin` (GitHub)** as the normal way to publish — **do not stop at “commit locally”** or assume another machine will push.
- Typical sequence on the VM: `cd /home/phill/wrrapd-GCP` → `git status` → `git add` (intended paths) → `git commit -m "…"` → **`git push`** → confirm the push succeeded (no “everything up-to-date” while the working tree is still dirty).
